label: ClearedParameterEvent
comment: The parameter event that is cleared by a ClearSimulationEvent.

label: SimulationEvents
comment: The simulation events to which this clear simulation event belongs to.

label: eventTime
comment: Execution time of the event. It is relative to the start of the simulation.

label: Terminal
comment: The terminal connecting to the bus to which the fault is applied.

label: FaultyEquipment
comment: Equipment carrying this fault.

label: FaultCauseTypes
comment: All types of fault cause.

label: occurredDateTime
comment: The date and time at which the fault occurred.

label: ClearSimulationEvent
comment: The event that clears this fault event.

label: SimulationEvents
comment: The simulation events to which this simulation fault event belongs to.

label: impedance
comment: Fault impedance. Its usage is described by 'kind'.

label: kind
comment: The kind of phase fault.

label: phases
comment: The phases participating in the fault. The fault connections into these phases are further specified by the type of fault.

label: rGround
comment: The resistance of the fault between phases and ground.

label: xLineToLine
comment: The reactance of the fault between phases.

label: rLineToLine
comment: The resistance of the fault between phases.

label: xGround
comment: The reactance of the fault between phases and ground.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: description
comment: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

label: ACLineSegment
comment: The line segment of this line fault.

label: lengthFromTerminal1
comment: The length to the place where the fault is located starting from terminal with sequence number 1 of the faulted line segment.

label: rampDuration
comment: Defines the duration of the ramp in case. Only used in case attribute changeKind is set to ramp.

label: integerParameterValue
comment: Integer parameter value. If this attribute is populated, booleanParameterValue and floatParameterValue will not be.

label: parameterName
comment: Identifies which parameter is changed during the event. It is used only in cases where IRI is not defined, e.g. an internal quantity of a model.

label: UsesParameterOf
comment: The equipment, dynamics model or signal that is used to define the parameter event.

label: changeKind
comment: Defines if the change is done in one step or using ramp.

label: floatParementerValue
comment: Floating point parameter value. If this attribute is populated, booleanParameterValue and integerParameterValue will not be.

label: booleanParameterValue
comment: Boolean parameter value. If this attribute is populated, integerParameterValue and floatParameterValue will not be.

label: parameterIRI
comment: Identifies which parameter is changed during the event. It can be an attribute of a class that inherits from IdentifiedObject. The parameter IRI (Internationalized Resource Identifier) is a Unicode string that conforms to the syntax defined in RFC 3987. The string is serialized as literal without language support.

label: eventTime
comment: Execution time of the event. It is relative to the start of the simulation.

label: SimulationEvents
comment: The simulation events to which this parameter event belongs to.

label: transformerPhaseTapControlPriority
comment:
Indicates if phase tap change control is applied on transformers. 0 means it is not used, i.e. it is disabled. 1 means it is enabled and indicates it is the highest priority among the following control related settings: transformerRatioTapControlPriority, transformerPhaseTapControlPriority, switchedShuntControlPriority and staticVarCompensatorControlPriority.
Allowed values are in the range [0,4].

label: voltageTolerance
comment:
The largest difference between actual and scheduled voltage magnitude for controlled node, in per unit of BaseVoltage, 
- at each node where voltage is subject to control to a set point, and 
- for which at least one of the devices participating in the control of bus voltage to its set point is not at a reactive power limit. 
It shall be less than the controlled bus voltage error convergence tolerance.

label: activePowerTolerance
comment: The active power tolerance for a given power flow solution. SvInjection.pInjection shall not be greater than this tolerance.

label: loadVoltageDependency
comment: Defines if voltage dependency of loads is considered. True means voltage dependency is considered. False means it is not considered.

label: respectActivePowerLimits
comment: Indicates if active power limits of the equipment are respected during power flow calculation. True means limits are respected. False means limits are ignored.

label: transformerRatioTapControlPriority
comment:
Indicates if ratio tap change control is applied on transformers. 0 means it is not used, i.e. it is disabled. 1 means it is enabled and indicates it is the highest priority among the following control related settings: transformerRatioTapControlPriority, transformerPhaseTapControlPriority, switchedShuntControlPriority and staticVarCompensatorControlPriority.
Allowed values are in the range [0,4].

label: interchangeControlEnabled
comment: Define if the interchange control is enabled during power flow calculation. True means area interchange control is enabled. False means it is disabled.

label: slackDistributionKind
comment: Defines slack distribution used in power flow calculation.

label: respectReactivePowerLimits
comment: Indicates if reactive power of limits of the equipment are respected during power flow calculation. True means limits are respected. False means limits are ignored.

label: staticVarCompensatorControlPriority
comment:
Indicates if control is applied on static var compensators. 0 means it is not used, i.e. it is disabled. 1 means it is enabled and indicates it is the highest priority among the following control related settings: transformerRatioTapControlPriority, transformerPhaseTapControlPriority, switchedShuntControlPriority and staticVarCompensatorControlPriority.
Allowed values are in the range [0,4].

label: reactivePowerTolerance
comment: The reactive power tolerance for a given power flow solution. SvInjection.qInjection shall not be greater than this tolerance.

label: shiftKind
comment: Defines type of scaling used to reach defined net-position.

label: voltageAngleLimit
comment: The maximum allowed voltage angle between two nodes for a given power flow solution.

label: flatStart
comment: True means that power flow used a flat start.

label: impedanceThreshold
comment: Zero impedance threshold used considered when calculating zero or low impendence branches. The per unit value is calculated with base power of 100 MW. If set to 0 the impedance threshold is not used.

label: switchedShuntControlPriority
comment:
Indicates if control is applied on switched shunts. 0 means it is not used, i.e. it is disabled. 1 means it is enabled and indicates it is the highest priority among the following control related settings: transformerRatioTapControlPriority, transformerPhaseTapControlPriority, switchedShuntControlPriority and staticVarCompensatorControlPriority.
Allowed values are in the range [0,4].

label: algorithmKind
comment: It defines the power flow algorithm.

label: signalKind
comment: Indicates the kind of the signal.

label: RecordedSignalOf
comment: The dynamics function block to which the singal belongs to.

label: SimulationConfiguration
comment: The simulation configuration set for which this signal recorder is recording.

label: RecordedSignal
comment: The signal that is recorded during the simulation.

label: RecordedSignalAt
comment: The terminal at which the signal is recorded.

label: duration
comment: Complete simulation duration relative to the start of the simulation.

label: integrationStepSize
comment: Indicates the integration step size. In case the integration step size is variable (i.e. isIntegrationStepSize=true), this value represents the initial integration step size used for the first iterations of the simulation prior activation of the adaptation os the step size.

label: maximumIntegrationStepSize
comment: Maximum integration step size. Used in case of variable integration step size (i.e. inIntegrationStepSizeVariable=true).

label: PowerFlowSettings
comment: The power flow settings that are part of the simulation settings.

label: minimumIntegrationStepSize
comment: Minimum integration step size. Used in case of variable integration step size (i.e. inIntegrationStepSizeVariable=true).

label: isIntegrationStepSizeVariable
comment: Indicates if the integration step size is variable or fixed. True means the integration step is variable. False means - fixed.

label: simulationResultsRecordedEvery
comment: Indicates the periodicity of recording of simulation results.
